  {
    "client_msg_id": "499d57b7-29b2-4fe3-a6da-e1c4b0948926",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I also like the resulting layout, let me reflect on why. I might be stating the obvious here, but anyway. Newspaper nostalgia aside, I like how you found a meaningful use for the advancement in screen technology. This layout would never have worked back on a 640*480 CRT, but today I'm on a 27 inch high-res screen (almost as large as a newspaper?), and yet many modern apps &amp; websites just waste that space, they use it for whitespace/margins and slightly smoother icons. Instead, you are fitting more content on screen! Browsing different articles by moving my gaze is inherently faster and easier than browsing by clicking a link and waiting for a new page to load.\n\nAnd I like that it works on phone too. The headlines are large enough to read, and then I can zoom in to read the rest. Double-tapping in Chrome on Android also does... some kind of zoom, maybe not exactly a \"column zoom\" like iOS, but still useful in this layout. Regarding ease-of-use, zooming/panning is in the same ballpark as tapping a link to a new article.\n\nAs a side effect, I got to read some interesting articles on your site, thanks!",
    "user": "U01NQ4945N1",
    "ts": "1614102995.020800",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "79a94a91f736",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2021-02-20/1799355166400_79a94a91f736df59b962_72.png",
      "first_name": "Emil",
      "real_name": "Emil H",
      "display_name": "Emil H",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "emil.hall",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "EPlm",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I also like the resulting layout, let me reflect on why. I might be stating the obvious here, but anyway. Newspaper nostalgia aside, I like how you found a meaningful use for the advancement in screen technology. This layout would never have worked back on a 640*480 CRT, but today I'm on a 27 inch high-res screen (almost as large as a newspaper?), and yet many modern apps & websites just waste that space, they use it for whitespace/margins and slightly smoother icons. Instead, you are fitting more content on screen! Browsing different articles by moving my gaze is inherently faster and easier than browsing by clicking a link and waiting for a new page to load.\n\nAnd I like that it works on phone too. The headlines are large enough to read, and then I can zoom in to read the rest. Double-tapping in Chrome on Android also does... some kind of zoom, maybe not exactly a \"column zoom\" like iOS, but still useful in this layout. Regarding ease-of-use, zooming/panning is in the same ballpark as tapping a link to a new article.\n\nAs a side effect, I got to read some interesting articles on your site, thanks!"
